  "text": "The first two competing methods, PRAGUE and BCLKG, are described in [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] respectively and summarized them in Section 1. Neither approach scales well to large datasets. In the first case, the bottleneck is the complexity of computing multi-alignments without guide trees and the vanishing probability that independent reconstructions agree. In the second case, the problem comes from slow mixing of the inference algorithm and the unregularized proliferation of parameters. For this reason, we built a third baseline that scales well in large datasets.",
